The paper discusses representation learning algorithms that are particularly suitable for robotics and control scenarios, which suggests that it could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. However, the focus on learning abstract features and the use of reinforcement learning also suggest that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the use of simulations and the potential application to computer vision tasks suggest that it could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category.
